text: Xenorhabdus indica is a bacterium from the genus of Xenorhabdus which has been isolated from the nematodes Steinernema thermophilum and Steinernema yirgalemense.UniProtDeutsche Sammlung von Mikroorganismen und Zellkulturen Xenorhabdus indica produces the Taxlllaids A–G. == References == == Further reading == * * * ==External links== *Type strain of Xenorhabdus indica at BacDive - the Bacterial Diversity Metadatabase Category:Bacteria described in 2009
title: Xenorhabdus indica
